l extension is made.";i:44;s:58:"Keep the other leg in its original position for stability.";i:45;s:50:"Slowly draw the one leg back to starting position.";i:46;s:41:"Repeat for both legs to count as one set.";i:47;s:25:"Wheelchair Leg Exercises.";i:48;s:78:"Sitting in a wheelchair can cause leg muscles to lose what strength they have.";i:49;s:115:"These limited mobility leg exercises will help you maintain and increase the muscle mass and strength in your legs.";i:50;s:157:"Chair exercises done while seated on a chair with back support are an excellent option for seniors who are frail at risk of falling or have limited mobility.";i:51;s:122:"The goal is to provide a steady base so your older adult stays safe while moving their arms and legs during their workout.";i:52;s:68:"Sit up on the edge of your chair with your legs out in front of you.";i:53;s:83:"Slowly lower your chest down toward your thighs to stretch both of your hamstrings.";i:54;s:74:"Hold the stretch for about 10 seconds then slowly lift your chest back up.";i:55;s:52:"Try to stretch your legs every time you work out to.";i:56;s:98:"As always sit up straight in your chair or wheelchair and engage those core muscles in your torso.";i:57;s:59:"Put your feet flat on the ground or flat on your footplate.";i:58;s:102:"Slowly lift one of your legs as far as you can comfortably manage and bend your knee back towards you.";i:59;s:123:"Sit on the edge of the chair lift your legs bend your legs at the knees and lean slightly back without rounding your spine.";i:60;s:72:"Bend your arms so your elbows are level with the bottom of your ribcage.";i:61;s:48:"Pull your navel in and twist slowly to the left.";i:62;s:30:"Inhale and twist to the right.";i:63;s:54:"Repeat the exercise dynamically 30 times on each side.";i:64;s:63:"Sit at the edge of your chair with your feet flat on the floor.";i:65;s:30:"Flex your foot up towards you.";i:66;s:31:"Raise your leg up a few inches.";i:67;s:42:"Perform these steps with the opposite leg.";i:68;s:87:"Using the back of a chair can add a healthy dose of Barre power to your chair workouts.";i:69;s:99:"There are numerous moves you can do but Perkins favors a backward extension to work the lower body.";i:70;s:108:"Stand with your feet hip-width apart behind a stationary chair holding onto the back with one or both hands.";i:71;s:112:"Surprisingly Effective Chair Workout for Legs and Core VIDEO By Sarah Purcell August 19 2020 Health and Fitness.";i:72;s:71:"I start most of my private clients with 10 minutes of breath awareness.";i:73;s:42:"Its amazing that we breathe automatically.";i:74;s:111:"What is not automatic is how our body changes shape to accommodate the pressure and volume change in our torso.";}}